15.31	Julian_Hawthorne	Julian Hawthorne	Julian Hawthorne (June 22, 1846â€“July 21, 1934) was an American writer and journalist, the son of novelist Nathaniel Hawthorne and Sophia Peabody. He wrote numerous poems, novels, short stories, mystery/detective fiction, essays, travel books, biographies and histories. As a journalist he reported on the Indian Famine for Cosmopolitan magazine, and the Spanish-American War for the New York Journal.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d1/Julian_Hawthorne.jpg/220px-Julian_Hawthorne.jpg
